name: GN-0000+GNR-010 00 Raiser
info: {'variation': None, 'notes': 'First PG kit released from the Anno Domini timeline. Features Gunpla LED Unit for eyes (two LR41 watch batteries included) and two GN Drives with lights and spinning flywheels (two CR2032 watch batteries included). GN Condensers on the arms and legs feature locking joints to support the weight of large weaponry and the 0 Raiser. Includes Setsuna F. Seiei and Saji Crossroad figurines. Initial release included 2 Way Stand Base for both 00 Gundam and 00 Raiser.', 'image-link': 'https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/8/82/4067108349_61d35f0e00.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20171009025721'}

name: RX-78-2 Gundam
info: {'variation': None, 'notes': 'First release of the Unleashed sub-line. Redesign of PG-01 with improved articulation and proportions. Features an array of metallic and chrome plated parts, plus metal parts and etching stickers. Uses dual-molded inner frame similar to that in Advanced MS Joint of Real Grade. Beam Rifle and Shield are mounted by magnets. Lighting unit powers up head and chest lights (requires two LR41 watch batteries). Beam Saber features LED gimmick that can alternately light up the thrusters when mounted on the backpack (one BR435 lithium battery included). Includes Amuro Ray and Sayla Mass figurines. Released as part of the Gunpla Evolution Project.', 'image-link': 'https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/c/c7/PGU_RX-78-2_Gundam.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20201215090216'}
notes: First release of the Unleashed sub-line. Redesign of PG-01 with improved articulation and proportions. Features an array of metallic and chrome plated parts, plus metal parts and etching stickers. Uses dual-molded inner frame similar to that in Advanced MS Joint of Real Grade. Beam Rifle and Shield are mounted by magnets. Lighting unit powers up head and chest lights (requires two LR41 watch batteries). Beam Saber features LED gimmick that can alternately light up the thrusters when mounted on the backpack (one BR435 lithium battery included). Includes Amuro Ray and Sayla Mass figurines. Released as part of the Gunpla Evolution Project.

First release in Bandai\'s "Gunpla Evolution Project" to prepare for the 40th anniversary of Gunpla in 2020.[7] Reissues from 2023 onwards are molded in Ecopla, which is plastic recycled from materials discarded during the production of regular Gunpla.', 'image-link': 'https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/f/f7/Hguc-zeta-gundam-gunpla-evolution-project-2017_%281%29.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20170330174059'}

Can accommodate HGUC-040's head to make the Zeta Zaku from episode 12 of Gundam ZZ. First release in Bandai's "Gunpla Evolution Project" to prepare for the 40th anniversary of Gunpla in 2020.[7] Reissues from 2023 onwards are molded in Ecopla, which is plastic recycled from materials discarded during the production of regular Gunpla.
